If it isn&#39;t necessary to _mutate_ the map, just atomically _replacing_ it, you could wrap the map in an `AtomicReference` and atomically replace the reference in a single go. The different threads wouldn&#39;t keep a reference to the map instance itself, but the surrounding `AtomicReference` instance.

```java
class Example {
    private final AtomicReference&lt;Map&lt;String, String&gt;&gt; mapRef = new AtomicReference&lt;&gt;(someInitialState);

    private void consumerThread() {
        // Get the current version of the map and look up a value from it.
        String value = mapRef.get().get(&quot;Hello&quot;);
        // Do something with value.
    }

    private void producerThread() {
        // Time to replace the whole map for all threads
        Map&lt;String, String&gt; newMap = calculateNewMap();
        mapRef.set(newMap);
    }
}
```

